As of Feb. 10, more than seventeen thousand medical personnel from 29 provinces and cities including Beijing, Guangdong and Zhejiang had gone to Hubei to support the health care, said Zheng Jin, a spokesman for the Shanghai Municipal Health and Safety Commission, on the afternoon of Feb. 11. At present, Shanghai has 937 medical personnel in Wuhan to participate in prevention and control work, including 198 doctors, 644 nurses.

This makes some Shanghai residents worry, Shanghai's local epidemic prevention and control as well as the daily diagnosis and treatment will have an impact?

In response, Zheng Jin believes that there are 3,853 medical institutions in Shanghai, with 77,700 doctors and 97,100 nurses, which can generally meet the needs of Shanghai for epidemic prevention and control and medical services.

As for the public's question, in recent days, the decrease in new cases, whether Shanghai "statistical caliber" change? Zheng Jin refuted this rumor: Shanghai has always been in accordance with national requirements, all cases of COVID-19 pneumonia found within the scope of this city are counted and regularly released, and people from other places in Shanghai have been diagnosed as new coronavirus pneumonia in this city, all included in the scope of the city's statistical release.

"The scope of our statistics has not changed, " Zheng said. "We will continue to improve the quality and level of our services, and thank you for your concern. "

As more than half of Shanghai's businesses resumed work on Feb. 10, he also reminded businesses to use air conditioning scientifically and regularly to prevent the spread of the disease.

Zheng Jin said that enterprises can only continue to operate with one of the following conditions: First, the use of all fresh air (circulating air is all outdoor fresh air) mode of operation, and second, the fan coil unit plus fresh air conditioning system, air conditioning, to ensure that the rooms are ventilated independently.

Even if companies are equipped with air conditioning that meet the above requirements, they must strictly follow the standard disinfection, cleaning and ventilation, she warned.

First of all, the Enterprise shall clean, disinfect or replace weekly the equipment or parts of the central air conditioning ventilation system, such as the open cooling tower, the filter net, the filter, the purifier, the air outlet, the air air handler, the surface cooler, the heater (wet) , the condensate Pan, etc. .

Second, after the end of each day's production or work, clean and disinfect the air and environment.

Finally, the enterprise must inform the central air-conditioning ventilation system in buildings or premises activities, wear masks, wash hands frequently, do personal protection, as much as possible open windows ventilation.
